webpackJsonp([0xbe2be99286947800],{"./node_modules/json-loader/index.js!./.cache/json/miscellaneous-interview-questions-for-junior-front-end-web-developers.json":function(e,o){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:"<p>The purpose of this article is to familiarize fresh Front-End Web Developers with text book questions. If you are just getting into the developer world there is a good chance you will feel nervous when interviewing for a developerâ€™s positon. Because of this, some relatively basic questions could feel more difficult than how they actually are. A good counter for this scenario is to be properly prepared.</p>\n<h2>Questions</h2>\n<p>Without further ado, here are a few questions that you could encounter:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>In the context of CSS styling can you explain what does <code>display-style: inline-block</code> stand for?</li>\n<li>If you have a <code>&#x3C;ul></code> element with several <code>&#x3C;li></code> elements, how would you go about setting up these elements in a row by using HTML and CSS?</li>\n<li>In CSS styling when would you use <code>float</code>s? How do they work?</li>\n<li>When would you use: <code>clear: both;</code>?</li>\n<li>What is Bootstrap? When would you use it? How does its grid system work?</li>\n<li>Explain the notion of responsive design and how it works? Use an example if you like.</li>\n<li>What is a DOM? What do you know about it?</li>\n<li>What is ECMAScript?</li>\n<li>What is jQuery and what is it commonly used for?</li>\n<li>What is the difference between <code>==</code> and <code>===</code> in JS?</li>\n<li>Can you enumerate all JavaScript data types?</li>\n<li>What is a callback function in JS and when would you use one?</li>\n<li>What is the difference between <code>undefined</code> and <code>null</code>?</li>\n<li>What is an async response?</li>\n<li>What does JSON stand for? What is it used for?</li>\n<li>How would you explain an API request?</li>\n<li>What APIs have you worked with?</li>\n<li>How would you send out/convert to JSON format?</li>\n<li>What is the difference between <code>GET</code> and <code>POST</code> when specifying an AJAX request?</li>\n<li>Have you worked with Photoshop as a front end developer? For what purpose?</li>\n<li>What software versioning system have you used? Could you describe how a workflow would look like in this system?</li>\n<li>What was the hardest project you ever worked on? Why was it difficult? If it is an application/algorithm can you explain how it works?</li>\n<li>How do you stay up to date with technology news?</li>\n</ol>",fields:{slug:"/miscellaneous/interview-questions-for-junior-front-end-web-developers/"},frontmatter:{title:"Interview Questions for Junior Front End Web Developers"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/miscellaneous/interview-questions-for-junior-front-end-web-developers/"}}}});
